text: Karolina Ciaszkiewicz-Lach (born 7 September 1979) is a Polish volleyball player. She played at the 2001 Women's European Volleyball Championship, 2004 FIVB World Grand Prix, and 2008 FIVB World Grand Prix. She played for Stal Bielsko-Biala and Aluprof. == References == Category:1979 births Category:Living people Category:Polish volleyball players
